                        },
                        "displayName": "Antoine Pitrou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "Well, you can have some sliced buffers and others unsliced, for example in a struct array. And you may not always know upfront if some buffers have been sliced...\r\n\r\nThat said, let's add this and we can improve it later (for example make it more flexible).\r\n",
